The filter syntax is not validated at all. For example, `--flagged` (which generates `"Flag/FlagStatus eq 'Flagged'"`) works, but a malicious EWS server could potentially inject XML via specially crafted filter values. While the filter values are user-supplied command arguments (not attacker-controlled), the approach of using `includes()` for filter parsing is fragile and not a proper parser.

